    <refsection id="Description_IdealTransformer">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            The ideal transformer is an ideal two-port resistive circuit element which is
            characterized by the following two equations:  v1 =  n * v2,   i2 = -n * i1,
            where n is a real number called the turns ratio.
        </para>
        <para>
        </para>
    </refsection>
